(Heller)
</taxonomicName>
</taxonomicName>
A, male pygofer, anal segments, and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, connective, lateral view; D, abdominal segment II and apodemes; E, aedeagus, lateral view; F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, style, lateroventral view; H, style, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BB636C4FFB6FB493EFAFF372027FECB" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">Pygofer dorsal margin with anterior dorsally directed lobe, caudal margin rounded. Anal tube with long acuminate process nearly reaching ventral margin of pygofer. Subgenital plate broadened distally in lateral view, with fine and dense setae on dorsal and ventral margin, as long as pygofer. Connective Y-shaped, with medial longitudinal keel. Style broad in apical half in lateral view, apex with lobe on each side, with dense setae on lateral surface subapically. Aedeagus simple, aedeagal shaft slender; dorsal apodeme developed; gonopore subapical.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB636C4FFB6FB493EFAFEEC276AFE26" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="572">Female genitalia with seventh sternite caudal margin produced, concave in middle. First valvulae broad, curved dorsally, apex pointed, with sculpture strigate on apical half. Second valvulae broad, straight, with 18–20 irregular dorsal teeth on apical half.</paragraph>
